text: Nathalie Joanne Emmanuel (born 2 March 1989) is a British actress. She began her acting career in theatre in the late 1990s. She had roles in West End productions including as the musical The Lion King. In 2006, she began her on- screen career by starring as Sasha Valentine in the soap opera Hollyoaks. After that, she appeared in British television series until her first movie appearance in Twenty8k. Emmanuel became famous around the world for her role as Missandei in the HBO fantasy series Game of Thrones (2013â€“2019). After that, she had supporting roles in Maze Runner: The Scorch Trials (2015) and its sequel Maze Runner: The Death Cure (2018), the Fast & Furious movies Furious 7 (2015), The Fate of the Furious (2017), F9 (2021) and Fast X (2023), and had lead roles in Army of Thieves (2021) and Megalopolis (2024). ==References== Category:1989 births Category:Living people Category:Actors from Essex
